Class SpectraChart

  • All Implemented Interfaces:

    public class SpectraChart
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.awt.event.ActionListener, javax.swing.event.ListSelectionListener, java.awt.event.ComponentListener, java.io.Serializable
    Implements a panel to show 30m and lmv spectra for different sources and molecules.

    1.0
    Author:
    T. Alonso Albi - OAN (Spain)

    • Constructor Detail

      • SpectraChart

        public SpectraChart(java.lang.String[] files,
            int w,
            int h)
        Basic constructor with 10 km/s of vel width, 10 arcsec of separation, first source and molecule found, and no map at startup.
        Parameters:
        files - 30m or lmv files to be scanned.
        w - Width.
        h - Height.

      • SpectraChart

        public SpectraChart(java.lang.String[] files,
            int w,
            int h,
            double sep,
            int vw,
            java.lang.String s,
            java.lang.String m,
            boolean map,
            boolean horiz)
        Full constructor.
        Parameters:
        files - 30m or lmv files to be scanned.
        w - Width.
        h - Height.
        sep - Separation between spectra in a map in arcsec.
        vw - Velocity width in km/s, should be greater than line width.
        s - Source name to be selected at startup.
        m - Molecule to be selected at startup.
        map - True to show a map at startup instead of a spectrum.
        horiz - True to show controls in horizontal, false for vertical.
